Reference Control ID	Reference Control Title	Reference Control Description
AC-1	Access Control Policy and Procedures	The organization develops, documents, and disseminates an access control policy that addresses purpose, scope, roles, responsibilities, management commitment, coordination among entities, and compliance. Policy is reviewed and updated annually or upon material change.
AC-2	Account Management	The organization manages information system accounts including establishment, activation, modification, review, disabling, and removal. Privileged accounts receive enhanced monitoring. Account inventory is maintained.
IA-2	Identification and Authentication (Multi-Factor)	The information system uniquely identifies and authenticates organizational users through multi-factor authentication for privileged accounts and remote network access. MFA mechanisms must be FIPS 140-2 validated where feasible.
IA-5	Authenticator Management	The organization manages information system authenticators by verifying initial authenticator content, establishing default content requirements, changing default authenticators upon installation, and establishing maximum and minimum lifetimes.
AU-2	Audit Events	The organization determines that the information system is capable of auditing security-relevant events. The organization coordinates the security audit function with other organizational entities requiring audit-related information.
AU-6	Audit Review, Analysis, and Reporting	The organization reviews and analyzes information system audit records weekly or more frequently for indications of inappropriate or unusual activity. Findings are reported to designated personnel.
SC-7	Boundary Protection	The information system monitors and controls communications at the external boundary of the system and at key internal boundaries within the system. Implements subnetworks for publicly accessible system components.
SC-13	Cryptographic Protection	The information system implements FIPS-validated or NSA-approved cryptography to protect the confidentiality and integrity of information at rest and in transit.
SC-28	Protection of Information at Rest	The information system protects the confidentiality and integrity of information at rest including data stored on mobile devices, removable media, and information system storage.
CM-3	Configuration Change Control	The organization determines the types of changes to the information system that are configuration-controlled, reviews proposed changes, approves or disapproves with explicit consideration for security impact, and documents change decisions.
CM-7	Least Functionality	The organization configures the information system to provide only essential capabilities and prohibits or restricts the use of non-essential functions, ports, protocols, and services.
RA-5	Vulnerability Monitoring and Scanning	The organization scans for vulnerabilities in the information system and hosted applications monthly or when new vulnerabilities are identified. Vulnerabilities are remediated within organizationally defined response timelines.



